zomato policy on bribing as per the employee code of conduct

Zomato's policy strictly prohibits any payment to anyone—including public officials, customers, merchants, consultants, or other third parties—to obtain or retain business, influence decisions, or gain an unfair advantage.  This explicitly includes bribes, kickbacks, and facilitation payments.

Zomato's internal policy strictly prohibits bribery, kickbacks, and facilitation payments to obtain or retain business, influence decisions, or gain an unfair advantage.  This applies to all payments made to any person, including public officials, customers, merchants, consultants, or any third party dealing with Zomato.
